## Target-repo conduct template

[assets/conduct.template.mdc](../../assets/conduct.template.mdc) is the default for brownfield init: always-on, links CONTEXT, proof from AGENTS.

## Factory vs target (Phase 2 pattern)

| Layer | Target brownfield repo | This skill repo (maintainers) |
|-------|------------------------|-------------------------------|
| Always-on minimum | conduct + safety (or Q13 combined conduct) | safety, conduct, repo-layout, skill-workflow |
| Glob-scoped | From `proposed_mdc_rules` only (stack, docs, …) | references, doc-style, mdc-authoring, **dual-publish** (`github-publish-lisp/**`) |
| Glossary link in rules | [`CONTEXT.md`](../../CONTEXT.md) | [`CONTEXT.md`](../../CONTEXT.md), [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md), [SKILL.md](../../SKILL.md) |

**Dual publish:** [.cursor/plans/dual-publish-architecture.md](../plans/dual-publish-architecture.md) — never blind-copy factory markdown `SKILL.md` into the Lisp ship tree.
| Phase 2 authority | [SKILL.md](../../SKILL.md) + [MDC-RULES-FORMAT.md](../../references/MDC-RULES-FORMAT.md) | Same — do not drift factory rules from SKILL without editing SKILL in a later slice |

## Legacy paths (scan, do not champion in new rules)

- `.cursorrules` — migrate content to `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` on merge
- `.windsurfrules`, `.clinerules` — inventory per annexes; port to scoped `.mdc` when converting

## Split rules (multi-mdc pattern)

Prefer several focused `.mdc` files over one giant always-on rule: conduct + safety (always-on minimum) + layout + workflow + glob-scoped detail (e.g. `references/**`, doc-style paths).
